# 🔥 If STILL no vxlan interface

Then we go one level deeper:

## 🔴 Check this (VERY important on CentOS)

```bash id="c2v7m1"
sysctl net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables
```

If result is:

```
0
```

👉 Fix:

```bash id="g7t2q9"
sudo sysctl -w net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables=1
sudo sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
```

Persist it:

```bash id="m8d4r2"
echo "net.bridge.bridge-nf-call-iptables=1" | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf
echo "net.ipv4.ip_forward=1" | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.conf
```

---

# 🧠 Why vxlan interface is missing

Docker only creates `vxlan0` when:

* nodes can communicate over UDP 4789
* firewall allows forwarding
* kernel networking is enabled

Right now → one of these is blocked.

---

